{
  "stem": "9538.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We found out later on these were these gas lorries, which they had in Treblinka as well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had some in Riga.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They gassed the people in these lorries and taken them already to the forests.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I come to that a little later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They marched us-- I can't tell you now.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was told now, from my home town, they had been back to Riga, to the ghetto, and to Skirotava.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's six kilometers through the-- we went six kilometers to this ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We came through a gate with watchtowers, electric wires, and old, shabby houses.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was a part of Riga.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They called it the Moscow of [NON-ENGLISH], which was a suburb of Riga where the underworld lived, you know, the poor people, the gypsies, the, the down-and-outs.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They had to vacate it and were given elegant houses and flats in Riga where they had taken the Latvian Jews out before we came.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Before we arrived on the 14th and 15th-- I'm not clear about the date-- of December, they had killed 40,000 Latvian Jews which were in that ghetto before us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That they did it-- this in three days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They had to leave the town of Riga.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They had to come into the ghetto and also the surrounding villages and towns of Riga.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The Jews all had to go into the Riga ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There were about 40,000 of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They were taken away in three different Aktionen, as we called it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The SS and the Latvian SS would come in with rifles, shooting at them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they had-- they're driven, literally driven like cattle, from the Riga ghetto in the Moscow of [NON-ENGLISH], yes--",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--to the Bikernieki Forest to Rumbula, which was a forest outside [SOBBING] Riga.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
